1
00:01:34,844 --> 00:01:36,095
There are days like that.

2
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:40,141
Days when I dreamed about you,

3
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:42,143
and on those days,

4
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:46,439
I can't help falling
into foolish little fantasies.

5
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:53,154
Like accidentally sharing a table
with you at a random restaurant,

6
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:58,243
or bumping into you
alone in an empty, late-night theater.

7
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:03,331
Just imagining it makes me happy.

8
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,460
And I imagine,

9
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:11,548
just once, a miracle like that

10
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:16,094
could happen to me too.

11
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:19,806
-The rule of law in Korea is dead!
-Dead!

12
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:24,227
-Punish those responsible!
-Punish them!

13
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,270
MINISTRY OF JUSTICEㅇ

14
00:02:25,353 --> 00:02:28,189
Re-arrest Lee Seong-ho immediately!

15
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,150
Arrest him!

16
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:34,070
-Investigate without a shred of doubt!
-Investigate!

17
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:36,447
Table tennis player Lee Seong-ho,

18
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:38,158
accused of blackmail and assault

19
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:41,327
against a junior teammate,
was acquitted today.

20
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:45,915
A petition urging a full retrial
has been posted.

21
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:49,002
With news of his hiring
a high-priced lawyer,

22
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:50,879
some legal experts say

23
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:53,840
with rising distrust,
that the court favors the privileged,

24
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:57,677
the outrage and criticism
are unlikely to subside anytime soon.

25
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,887
Attorney Maeng Se-na,

26
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:01,306
public backlash
against this ruling is fierce.

27
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:02,432
As defense attorney,

28
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:04,642
what's your view on the trial outcome?

29
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,979
COURT

30
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:12,775
The significance lies
in revealing the truth.

31
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:15,612
The prosecution's claim of special assault

32
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,614
was not upheld.

33
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:21,200
-Justice in Korea is dead!
-Dead!

34
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:25,121
Regardless of guilt or innocence,

35
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:27,373
the defendant deeply regrets

36
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,126
causing public concern.

37
00:03:31,085 --> 00:03:34,505
Additionally, please be advised
that spreading false information

38
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:37,008
differing from reality
may result in legal action.

39
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:37,967
That is all.

40
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:43,264
PLAYER LEE SEONG-HO
ACQUITTED OF SPECIAL ASSAULT CHARGES

41
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:50,772
That's our Attorney Maeng!

42
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:53,524
Unstoppable and undefeated.

43
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,360
Truly amazing!

44
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:58,947
She looks so good on screen.

45
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,782
She's gorgeous!

46
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,660
Don't get too excited.

47
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:05,870
People outside are going wild,

48
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,705
saying the poor victim

49
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:09,374
should file an appeal.

50
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,626
This is bad.

51
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:14,212
Public opinion is emotion,
but the law is logic.

52
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:17,340
Isn't it so? We speak through results.

53
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:20,260
If it came out not guilty,
that's the correct answer.

54
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:23,888
-All right.
-I'm Prosecutor Kim Gi-wook…

55
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,641
The prosecutor looks miserable.

56
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:28,309
He's going to get chewed out.

57
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:29,727
PROSECUTION BRIEFING

58
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:31,437
Not the only one she crushed.

59
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,273
Why did this kind of article come out?

60
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:35,566
Are you even prosecutors?

61
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:39,320
They even held an emergency meeting
at the Seoul Central District Office.

62
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:41,698
By the way, how did she win that case?

63
00:04:42,323 --> 00:04:44,659
There was CCTV footage
and witness testimony.

64
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:47,203
That's why she made partner at that age.

65
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,247
ATTORNEY MAENG SE-NA
CONGRATULATIONS ON BECOMING PARTNER

66
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:52,750
That's a talent too.
By taking the most brutal cases,

67
00:04:52,834 --> 00:04:55,837
she raised her name and her value.

68
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,422
I wonder how much she's made.

69
00:04:57,505 --> 00:05:00,091
-I'm jealous.
-Feeling jealous?

70
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:02,719
She takes all the hate the world throws.

71
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,263
Sometimes she doesn't even seem human.

72
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:07,765
More like an AI, an android.

73
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:09,100
No emotions,

74
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:14,022
no dating, no family, no friends.
She just works all the time.

75
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:18,568
Unless she's a robot,
no human could live like that.

76
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:21,487
That's a very interesting theory.

77
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:27,201
Earlier today, the case prosecutor said…

78
00:05:28,619 --> 00:05:29,579
Attorney Maeng!

79
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:31,164
When did you get here?

80
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:35,460
Twenty-nine minutes ago.

81
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,421
Check for missing copies, please.

82
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:41,215
Hey.

83
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:45,136
You should've said something
when you arrived.

84
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:47,597
Everyone's been waiting
to congratulate you.

85
00:05:48,931 --> 00:05:51,809
Thank you,
but I am a bit busy today.

86
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:56,397
Please forward the brief
from the previous embezzlement case.

87
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:57,815
Wait, hold on.

88
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:02,487
The boss set this up to congratulate you.

89
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:06,282
Can't you read the room?

90
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:07,700
That's fine.

91
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:10,453
I just thanked him a moment ago.

92
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:12,497
-Yes, I heard her.
-But…

93
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:16,876
You're not planning to lecture me
for skipping a gathering

94
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:20,171
I wasn't even informed about, are you?

95
00:06:21,464 --> 00:06:23,174
-I'm just--
-I'm sorry,

96
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:26,177
but I can't rearrange my schedule.

97
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:27,887
And I'd rather not waste anyone's time

98
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:31,015
-by celebrating my personal achievements.
-Right.

99
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:37,980
This is why I like her.

100
00:06:38,856 --> 00:06:41,818
But it's a happy day,
so just take a moment to cool off--

101
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,903
I'm sorry, but I must decline.

102
00:06:45,321 --> 00:06:46,656
-My shift is over.
-Huh?

103
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:48,866
Already?

104
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:51,202
Then, I'll see you tomorrow.

105
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:56,124
At least grab a bite.
You always skip your meals.

106
00:06:56,207 --> 00:07:00,294
Is that really enough?
Should I pack this for you, then?

107
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:01,963
What a brat.

108
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:06,342
Why won't you eat it? It's expensive.

109
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,149
From listener 3751,

110
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:24,110
Do Ra-ik's "It's Me"

111
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:25,987
has finally dropped.

112
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:29,824
I'd love to share
this exciting first moment.

113
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:31,159
Today's new release.

114
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:35,163
Do Ra-ik of Gold Boys
has returned with a solo comeback.

115
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:37,957
With our final song, "It's Me,"

116
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,501
I hope you all have a wonderful evening.

117
00:07:56,434 --> 00:07:59,353
I walk a path that's neither
Warm nor cold

118
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:01,981
After walking alone for so long

119
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:07,236
I start to mistake the creeping unease

120
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,655
Sometimes it feels like
It'll never end

121
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:13,784
And even the broken moments of rest
Were never truly mine

122
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:17,497
But anyone would feel the same

123
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:22,627
I can't live mindlessly

124
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:28,090
The way the world wants me to

125
00:08:29,091 --> 00:08:35,389
I'm still me, just as I've always been

126
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,557
Not once…

127
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:39,143
You have a message from Like.

128
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:41,896
I'm streaming, no DMs.

129
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,147
SMING: Repeatedly streaming a song
to boost its chart ranking

130
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:46,150
I'm still the same as you know me

131
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:48,694
There is nothing less

132
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:51,447
There is nothing more

133
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:56,327
Nice.

134
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:59,747
It's me

135
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:06,921
Let's get started.

136
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:09,924
Our cutie.

137
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,051
We'll spoil you.

138
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,261
DO RA-IK

139
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:15,304
ADD TO PLAYLIST

140
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,436
FANJJAEK

141
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,980
RA-IK SOLO

142
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:25,982
RA-IK SOLO COMEBACK

143
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:34,156
CONGRATS ON RA-IK'S SOLO

144
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,324
RA-IK SOLO COMEBACK

145
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,285
YOU ARE THE BEST, RA-IK!

146
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:48,754
DO RA-IK

147
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:02,226
DO RA-IK'S "IT'S ME" VIDEO PHOTOSHOOT

148
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,353
What is this?

149
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:06,564
He looks like a statue.

150
00:10:12,486 --> 00:10:13,321
Please notify me

151
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,198
of Do Ra-ik's photoshoots

152
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:18,659
like an emergency alert.

153
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:27,293
Do Ra-ik, "It's me" is a total hit.

154
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:30,087
I heard you won the case.

155
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:31,839
-We should celebrate.
-I'm busy.

156
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:36,761
I brought this too.

157
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:42,516
Just leave it there.

158
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:46,228
What about me? Am I supposed to starve?

159
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:47,938
I brought it all the way here.

160
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:07,875
Did you eat before all that?

161
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:10,002
Food isn't the priority.

162
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,421
It's the historic day
Ra-ik dropped his solo.

163
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:13,923
Did you hit the like button?

164
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,841
We must support him however we can.

165
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,093
Please.

166
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:19,470
Mind your own business first.

167
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:22,556
The whole internet is blowing up
over the Lee Seong-ho case,

168
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,684
saying things like "They freed a devil"
and "She just wants money."

169
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:27,520
It's nothing new. I won, that's all.

170
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,481
You should've just made
one statement at the photo line.

171
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:33,651
The assault was nothing
but the victim's word,

172
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:36,570
and that so-called CCTV evidence
was just a light shove.

173
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:39,698
I gathered all the evidence
to counter it for you.

174
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,784
I already said everything in court.

175
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:45,538
Which is why people keep saying
you only care about money.

176
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:50,376
Truth is, every other lawyer
was too scared to take the case,

177
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:51,419
but you took it on.

178
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:55,214
People only see and believe
what they want.

179
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:58,259
No matter what I say,
they won't believe me.

180
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,804
I just do my job.

181
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,723
Because in the end,

182
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:07,643
the truth always comes out in court.

183
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,480
And people aren't

184
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:13,732
entirely wrong.

185
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:15,025
Money is part of it.

186
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:17,528
When I take tough cases, I earn more.

187
00:12:17,611 --> 00:12:21,615
And the more I earn,
the more I can support Ra-ik.

188
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:25,035
You get all that hate, work so hard,
and spend it all on him.

189
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,079
You don't think it's a waste?

190
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:29,498
Waste? I feel bad I can't give him more.

191
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:36,297
What's so great about him anyway?

192
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:38,966
He looks pretty much the same as I do.

193
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:40,634
Chung-jae!

194
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:42,344
What you are saying is…

195
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:46,849
You're basically saying

196
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:51,979
a mud lump squeezed by a toddler
and thrown around

197
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:53,647
is the same

198
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,191
as Michelangelo's David

199
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:58,194
in an Italian museum.

200
00:12:59,069 --> 00:13:01,197
Where's the mirror? Go look at yourself.

201
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:03,949
Or get your eyes checked.
You must be sick.

202
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:08,078
He just looks fancy on the outside.

203
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:09,872
He's just a person like us.

204
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:12,416
He poops, farts,

205
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,502
and gets chili flakes stuck
in his teeth.

206
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,712
No, Ra-ik is different.

207
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,132
These are all the same person.

208
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,717
Why are you hoarding this stuff?

209
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:25,179
Don't touch it with greasy hands.

210
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:31,685
Chung-jae,

211
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,022
you really don't know what love is.

212
00:13:36,148 --> 00:13:38,526
I know it better than you,
a lifelong single.

213
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,822
You don't know anything.

214
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,158
Love is something

215
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:49,245
that destroys any sense of logic.

216
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:51,997
Sure, I've told myself,
"I should stop buying these,"

217
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:54,083
and "Why am I buying another one?"

218
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:55,918
How could I not?

219
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,003
It's this pretty!

220
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:01,715
You just go for it first.

221
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:07,763
Love doesn't need a reason, it never has.

222
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:14,687
Even knowing well
that no answer will come back.

223
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:18,107
Just shouting his name out loud

224
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,317
is enough to fill your whole heart.

225
00:14:21,068 --> 00:14:24,822
Like a flawless diamond
admired simply for existing,

226
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,742
just its presence alone

227
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:30,953
makes every explanation unnecessary.

228
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:36,458
To give all of yourself
without a hint of regret…

229
00:14:38,627 --> 00:14:40,462
that is what true love is.

230
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:42,464
Oppa!

231
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,719
Ra-ik!

232
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,831
How did this happen again?

233
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:18,125
I told you to tighten security.

234
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:20,461
I switched to the best security company,

235
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:22,004
but your fans are so…

236
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:31,680
Let's go.

237
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:34,350
You haven't told him about it yet, right?

238
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,020
It's fine.

239
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:40,397
He'll understand if I tell him.

240
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:44,068
Just tell him now.

241
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:49,990
How am I going on stage
with hair like this?

242
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,241
Why am I the only one trying?

243
00:15:51,325 --> 00:15:53,619
Why am I always the only one who cares?

244
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:57,247
Let me check my outfit.

245
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:04,088
I'm going to the car.

246
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,255
Ra-ik!

247
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:09,051
Why the car? It's your solo debut.
You have to go on stage.

248
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:10,594
Then prepare things properly.

249
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:13,389
Hair, makeup, and outfit,
none of them is right.

250
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:15,391
How am I supposed to perform like this?

251
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:16,642
We can redo everything.

252
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:19,061
-Come on, let's--
-No, I don't need it.

253
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,106
Move.

254
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:24,358
-I said move.
-Wait, hold on.

255
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,861
Let's talk for a second.

256
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:32,324
Excuse us, we need to talk for a moment.

257
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:35,703
Let's step out for a moment.

258
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:47,089
Move out, seriously!

259
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,807
I'm sorry, it's really my fault.

260
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:58,017
Why didn' t you tell me?

261
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,519
-I knew you wouldn't come.
-I shouldn't have.

262
00:17:00,602 --> 00:17:02,730
I said from the start
that I don't do music shows.

263
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:05,107
Given my seniority,
after all I conceded,

264
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:07,943
shouldn't the company support me too?

265
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,903
How could you give the ending

266
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:12,239
to those TMB or whatever they are?

267
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:14,992
You should've said, "If you're not giving
the ending, back off.

268
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:16,869
He's got plenty of stages waiting."

269
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:21,081
If you can't handle that,
why make me come here?

270
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,959
I couldn't help it.
TMB is huge these days.

271
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:31,925
They're huge?
I've never even heard of them.

272
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:34,470
They're not huge, just rookies.

273
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:36,722
It's your first solo,

274
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:39,808
so of course your solo power
can't match the group's…

275
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,895
But compared to your fandom,

276
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:44,897
they're tiny.

277
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:49,318
Honestly, if you were Ra-ik of Gold Boys,

278
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:51,862
that would be different.
But this is your first solo.

279
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:54,364
That's why we got you on music shows.

280
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,742
But with new rookies blowing up,
no one can stop that.

281
00:17:56,825 --> 00:17:59,620
Not me, not the CEO, not the company.

282
00:17:59,703 --> 00:18:00,621
Only you can.

283
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,795
They said to stand by.

284
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,130
You're still pretty good.

285
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:12,800
I'm fully fired up now.

286
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:16,720
What are you doing?
Bring the staff in, we don't have time.

287
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:18,847
Yes.

288
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:23,727
Come in! Hurry!

289
00:18:24,353 --> 00:18:27,231
My flame, who's tall, handsome,

290
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:29,274
and an amazing actor,

291
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:31,610
was actually the main vocalist
of a 12-year band.

292
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:35,322
The versatile Ra-ik from Gold Boys
excels at both bass and vocals,

293
00:18:35,405 --> 00:18:38,534
has now returned as a solo artist.

294
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:40,828
He says it shows his true self, sincerely.

295
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,788
Mr. Do Ra-ik, please stand by.

296
00:18:42,871 --> 00:18:44,998
Let's hear it now, "It's Me."

297
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:49,294
I walk a path
That's neither warm nor cold

298
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:51,713
After walking alone for so long

299
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:57,010
I start to mistake the creeping unease

300
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,763
Sometimes it feels like
It'll never end

301
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:03,392
And even the broken moments of rest
Were never truly mine

302
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:06,979
But anyone would feel the same…

303
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:09,731
One day, I swear I'll kill that bastard.

304
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,984
No, I'll kill him.

305
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:15,404
They have no idea, huh?

306
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:18,532
That lunatic is actually a total psycho.

307
00:19:18,615 --> 00:19:20,200
If they knew, they wouldn't be here.

308
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:25,164
I'm still me, just as I've always been

309
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:30,377
Not once have I ever been
Anyone but myself

310
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:32,713
I'm still

311
00:19:32,796 --> 00:19:36,049
The same as you know me

312
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,385
There is nothing less

313
00:19:38,468 --> 00:19:40,929
There is nothing more

314
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:44,016
The purpose of this amendment

315
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:47,436
is to recalculate
the defendants' breach of trust

316
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:51,440
based on the valuation report.

317
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:54,318
There is a gap between the actual value

318
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:57,821
and the purchase price,
so I'll explain them one by one.

319
00:19:57,905 --> 00:20:01,909
The actual value of the Areum real estate
purchased by the defendants…

320
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:04,786
Let me see.

321
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:08,624
…has been revised upward
from 50 million won.

322
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,000
to 1.46 billion won.

323
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,545
Accordingly, the difference in price

324
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:17,966
has also been revised,
from 640 million won to 430 million won.

325
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:21,553
Your Honor, I'm sorry,

326
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,430
but could you please instruct
defense counsel

327
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:26,934
to refrain from actions
that impede the proceedings?

328
00:20:28,268 --> 00:20:30,854
The one obstructing this trial
is the prosecution.

329
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:32,147
I, as defense counsel,

330
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,067
have an unavoidable reason,
chronic respiratory condition.

331
00:20:35,692 --> 00:20:38,528
But the prosecutor
is deliberately delaying the trial

332
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:41,323
by abusing
the indictment amendment system.

333
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:44,159
It's just to make the allegations clearer…

334
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:45,994
So, is it clearer now?

335
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:48,038
From what I see here,

336
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:51,375
the date, location,
and method of the offense

337
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,876
have not been supplemented.

338
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,671
You were told to file before the hearing,

339
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:58,215
yet you filed on the day of the hearing,

340
00:20:58,298 --> 00:21:00,467
-without proper preparation…
-Your Honor,

341
00:21:01,134 --> 00:21:03,387
under Article 27, Paragraph 3
of the Criminal Act,

342
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:06,306
it is stated that every citizen
has the right to a prompt trial.

343
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:09,726
For the sake of the defendant,
who is suffering from a prolonged trial,

344
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:13,105
I earnestly request that the court

345
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:16,400
proceed without further delay.

346
00:21:24,866 --> 00:21:26,827
South entrance of the West Building.

347
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,293
I'm fine.

348
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,352
Prosecutor Kwak!

349
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,062
-What are you doing here?
-Here.

350
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:56,857
-I came for the trial, and--
-And?

351
00:21:56,940 --> 00:22:00,027
Something came up, so I need to spare time
for the woman who went inside.

352
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:01,403
A woman? You?

353
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:03,613
Is she pretty?

354
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:04,906
No, not like that.

355
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,326
Some woman did this to my coffee

356
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:10,579
and then walked in there,
and my shoes are a mess.

357
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:15,042
-Really?
-She needs to learn

358
00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:17,002
that a simple apology
doesn't cover the damage.

359
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:18,211
Right?

360
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:22,591
Some people only learn basic manners

361
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:24,843
when you teach them.

362
00:22:24,926 --> 00:22:27,220
Because they grew up
without learning basic manners.

363
00:22:27,304 --> 00:22:28,805
Right.

364
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:31,433
Could you tell the person inside
to come out quickly?

365
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:33,310
I'm in a hurry.

366
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:34,770
There's no one inside.

367
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,834
I said not to call me
for things like this.

368
00:22:57,918 --> 00:22:59,169
Am I a taxi?

369
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:01,046
If I drive now, it's going to be jammed.

370
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:02,506
Then take the subway.

371
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:05,008
Double the premium taxi surcharge.

372
00:23:26,321 --> 00:23:28,907
What if you get vocal nodules again?

373
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:31,118
I told you not to strain yourself.

374
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:34,037
Just hold on until the autograph session.

375
00:23:34,913 --> 00:23:36,998
If fans find out, they'll freak out.

376
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:45,590
Ra-ik!

377
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,801
I know it's you.

378
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:50,595
Why aren't you talking, huh?

379
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:01,231
This is Do Ra-ik's number, right?
I love you, Do Ra-ik.

380
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:03,275
How can you treat a fan like this?
My love, Do Ra-ik.

381
00:24:03,358 --> 00:24:04,693
You're so mean, Ra-ik, reply to me.

382
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:07,320
I'm watching everything.
You're reading my messages, right?

383
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:09,447
I know it all.
You changed your home password.

384
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:11,533
Tell me too.
Why am I the only one left out?

385
00:24:25,338 --> 00:24:26,673
TO. YOO-JIN

386
00:24:28,592 --> 00:24:29,759
Here it is.

387
00:24:29,843 --> 00:24:31,761
-Thank you.
-Get home safe.

388
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,263
Ra-ik, you're so handsome!

389
00:24:37,475 --> 00:24:38,894
-What's your name?
-I'm Hye-joo.

390
00:24:43,481 --> 00:24:46,193
-Your name is Hye-joo?
-Yes, it's Sim Hye-joo.

391
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:50,030
That's a pretty name.

392
00:24:52,324 --> 00:24:54,618
Ra-ik, you're really handsome.

393
00:24:54,701 --> 00:24:57,662
Thank you, Hye-joo, thanks for coming.

394
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:00,332
Thank you.

395
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,633
Ra-ik.

396
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,301
Hey, Ra-ik!

397
00:25:16,932 --> 00:25:18,225
What's your name?

398
00:25:18,308 --> 00:25:20,310
You still don't remember my name?

399
00:25:20,393 --> 00:25:22,437
It's been years.

400
00:25:23,063 --> 00:25:25,857
What's your IQ?

401
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:27,025
Sorry.

402
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:30,070
-Tell me again, and I'll remember it.
-Yeah?

403
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:31,905
I can't just tell you.

404
00:25:31,988 --> 00:25:34,491
If you tell me what I want to know,
I'll tell you.

405
00:25:37,452 --> 00:25:40,038
What do you want to know?

406
00:25:40,121 --> 00:25:40,956
Your phone number.

407
00:25:42,499 --> 00:25:44,042
Why do you keep changing it?

408
00:25:44,918 --> 00:25:47,587
Give me your number, didn't you hear me?

409
00:25:47,671 --> 00:25:51,883
Give me your phone number!

410
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:54,803
Hey, give me your number!

411
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:56,179
Hey!

412
00:25:56,263 --> 00:25:57,430
Ra-ik, you!

413
00:25:57,514 --> 00:26:00,308
Do you know how much money I spent on you?

414
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:02,394
Ra-ik, I'm sorry!

415
00:26:02,477 --> 00:26:03,979
I was wrong!

416
00:26:04,062 --> 00:26:07,399
I love you!

417
00:26:08,275 --> 00:26:11,069
Ra-ik!

418
00:26:12,112 --> 00:26:15,073
Do Ra-ik, I love you.

419
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:44,185
Ra-ik, what's going on?

420
00:26:47,564 --> 00:26:48,523
Open the door.

421
00:26:49,774 --> 00:26:51,067
I'm fine, just go.

422
00:26:53,069 --> 00:26:55,155
Okay, I'll wait outside.
Come out when you're ready.

423
00:27:16,801 --> 00:27:19,262
Hey, drop me off up there.

424
00:27:19,346 --> 00:27:20,680
By this pillar?

425
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:25,727
Thanks, I'll go in first.

426
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:30,940
Excuse me.

427
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:35,779
Thank you.

428
00:27:42,494 --> 00:27:43,620
So clumsy.

429
00:27:50,043 --> 00:27:52,253
Ra-ik was really cool today, right?

430
00:27:52,337 --> 00:27:53,671
He's even better in person.

431
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:56,132
The camera can't capture it all.

432
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:12,148
DO RA-IK, I LOVE YOU

433
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,208
I missed the autograph session,

434
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:32,168
and the music show too.

435
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:36,047
If I end up missing the solo concert too…

436
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:40,677
Don't cry looking like that.
It's embarrassing.

437
00:28:41,386 --> 00:28:43,012
Why do you show up looking like that?

438
00:28:43,096 --> 00:28:44,681
You're here to see your flame.

439
00:28:47,642 --> 00:28:49,436
People must not recognize me.

440
00:28:50,186 --> 00:28:53,356
I get every insult
for defending all kinds of scumbags.

441
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,858
What if someone recognizes me?

442
00:28:54,941 --> 00:28:56,943
If they find out
someone like me is his fan,

443
00:28:57,026 --> 00:28:58,987
he could get criticized too.

444
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:00,905
And if he knew, he might be disappointed.

445
00:29:00,989 --> 00:29:02,615
That guy wouldn't recognize you

446
00:29:02,699 --> 00:29:06,035
even if you showed up
in a bright red evening dress.

447
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:07,370
You look really ordinary.

448
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:13,877
It's fine.

449
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:15,754
I'm fine

450
00:29:17,213 --> 00:29:18,339
just watching…

451
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:21,676
from afar…

452
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:24,763
just being able to look at him is enough.

453
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:28,558
That's really enough.

454
00:30:11,226 --> 00:30:13,978
I woke up at four, stopped by the salon,

455
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:16,898
went to the music show for the recording,

456
00:30:16,981 --> 00:30:19,734
then went to the evening autograph
session, and I only just got back.

457
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,365
I didn't know
there was still a fan meeting left.

458
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:30,662
Come out.

459
00:30:32,455 --> 00:30:35,166
If you're not out here in three seconds,
I'll really get mad.

460
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,377
One,

461
00:30:38,628 --> 00:30:39,879
two,

462
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:41,422
three!

463
00:30:45,593 --> 00:30:48,429
Why aren't you sleeping today…

464
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:53,059
But why do you drink so much?

465
00:30:53,142 --> 00:30:54,602
Don't you care about your health?

466
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:56,938
Yeah, you've started promotions now.

467
00:30:57,021 --> 00:30:59,941
You need to manage yourself
or you'll look swollen again.

468
00:31:04,237 --> 00:31:06,614
This is something like a diffuser.

469
00:31:11,286 --> 00:31:15,373
-Move out!
-We really had an appointment to meet.

470
00:31:17,667 --> 00:31:18,585
For real!

471
00:31:18,668 --> 00:31:21,421
-We have not been informed of anything.
-No, really.

472
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:25,258
Ra-ik promised to make us Kimchi Udon.

473
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:54,454
Why? Why not put soap
while you're at it?

474
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:56,789
Give me a towel.

475
00:32:05,548 --> 00:32:06,507
Hey.

476
00:32:08,509 --> 00:32:11,220
You call yourselves fans when you barge
into someone's home?

477
00:32:11,846 --> 00:32:14,599
You're the same as cockroaches.

478
00:32:15,183 --> 00:32:17,101
Dirty, disgusting, and repulsive!

479
00:32:17,185 --> 00:32:18,853
The company could've handled this,

480
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:21,147
but you couldn't hold it in
and created this mess?

481
00:32:21,230 --> 00:32:23,483
Do you know how much money
we spent to contain it?

482
00:32:23,566 --> 00:32:25,526
Here, the towel.

483
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:27,612
What's wrong with calling a criminal
a criminal?

484
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:30,031
Don't I earn this much for you?

485
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:34,827
You really think
you're worth that much, don't you?

486
00:32:35,745 --> 00:32:37,413
I can tell by all you're wearing.

487
00:32:38,247 --> 00:32:40,917
I've never seen that ring,
did you get it new?

488
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:44,087
Gold keeps going up in value
if you hold onto it.

489
00:32:44,170 --> 00:32:46,422
You on the other hand keep going down.

490
00:32:49,175 --> 00:32:51,302
You haven't checked yet?

491
00:32:52,053 --> 00:32:53,846
You dropped to tenth yesterday.

492
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:54,889
What?

493
00:33:00,061 --> 00:33:03,106
You know how important
this solo promotion is, right?

494
00:33:03,189 --> 00:33:06,150
Thanks to you cursing out fans,

495
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:10,321
we nearly lost every ad deal,
you know that?

496
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:12,657
They weren't fans, they were stalkers.

497
00:33:12,740 --> 00:33:15,159
They snuck into my home. I'm the victim.

498
00:33:15,243 --> 00:33:19,455
I know, you must've been shocked too.

499
00:33:19,539 --> 00:33:21,582
They go in and out of your house
more than you,

500
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:23,835
and even steal your underwear.

501
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:28,589
Yeah, it must be driving you crazy.
I get it.

502
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:32,510
But the moment you show all your emotions,

503
00:33:32,593 --> 00:33:36,806
you're no longer Do Ra-ik of Gold Boys,
you're just the human Do Ra-ik.

504
00:33:36,889 --> 00:33:39,517
People don't want the human Do Ra-ik!

505
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:43,938
You can only deserve all of this
if you keep that perfect image.

506
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:47,650
No swearing, no drinking, understand?

507
00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:52,363
If you understand,

508
00:33:52,447 --> 00:33:55,116
then wash up and go practice.
The concert is soon.

509
00:33:58,119 --> 00:34:00,413
-Take him straight to the practice room.
-Yes, sir.

510
00:34:01,789 --> 00:34:03,166
Then…

511
00:34:05,001 --> 00:34:07,628
when can I finally live freely?

512
00:34:09,797 --> 00:34:13,342
Since I met you when I was ten,
I've only done exactly what I was told.

513
00:34:14,010 --> 00:34:17,722
When will I be able to say
I'm hurting when I'm hurt,

514
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:21,809
and tell people who wronged me
to stop tormenting me?

515
00:34:21,893 --> 00:34:25,104
When can I live as the human Do Ra-ik?

516
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:30,276
Well.

517
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:32,779
If you keep this up,

518
00:34:33,446 --> 00:34:36,240
that day might come sooner.

519
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:38,743
The day when nobody loves you anymore.

520
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:15,947
PLEASE WAIT A MOMENT

521
00:35:24,872 --> 00:35:25,915
HIGH TRAFFIC DETECTED

522
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,251
It's coming!

523
00:35:28,334 --> 00:35:29,418
It's opening!

524
00:35:30,002 --> 00:35:32,672
It opened!

525
