574
00:39:45,674 --> 00:39:46,592
Stop rushing me.

575
00:39:46,675 --> 00:39:48,969
Where on earth did you go?

576
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:52,223
I'm entering the parking lot.
Have Sang-beom come out.

577
00:39:53,432 --> 00:39:55,476
-What did he say?
-Go to the parking lot now, hurry.

578
00:39:56,102 --> 00:39:57,395
Yes.

579
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:47,278
Excuse me.

580
00:40:49,238 --> 00:40:50,281
It's you.

581
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:01,333
Hey, money first.

582
00:41:12,303 --> 00:41:15,181
-What is this?
-What do you think?

583
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:18,058
You've been caught
committing illegal ticket scalping

584
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:20,895
that harms the concert ecosystem
and consumer rights.

585
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:23,022
So you will now be escorted
to the police station

586
00:41:23,105 --> 00:41:25,483
to face the full extent of the law.

587
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:29,695
Hey!

588
00:41:30,237 --> 00:41:32,823
Under Article 3, Paragraph 2, Clause 4
of the Misdemeanor Punishment Act

589
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:35,326
selling tickets at a premium
is punishable by a fine

590
00:41:35,409 --> 00:41:37,786
of up to 200,000 Won,
detention, or a minor fine.

591
00:41:53,219 --> 00:41:54,803
Hey, isn't that Ra-ik's manager?

592
00:41:54,887 --> 00:41:56,931
Where have you been?

593
00:41:57,014 --> 00:41:58,015
Everyone is…

594
00:41:59,391 --> 00:42:00,434
It's Ra-ik!

595
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:08,526
There's a staff passage over there.

596
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:10,986
-Go first, hurry!
-Where?

597
00:42:14,114 --> 00:42:15,574
Don't chase him!

598
00:42:21,038 --> 00:42:22,831
Why? Did you lose him?

599
00:42:23,499 --> 00:42:24,959
With those long legs!

600
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:27,086
You go that way, I'll go this way.

601
00:42:27,795 --> 00:42:29,255
-Call me when you find him.
-Sure.

602
00:42:48,607 --> 00:42:49,817
Where is the passage?

603
00:42:56,115 --> 00:42:58,117
Why isn't he picking up?

604
00:43:03,914 --> 00:43:05,499
Where do you think you're running?

605
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:25,978
Where is he?

606
00:43:27,104 --> 00:43:29,690
This way.

607
00:43:35,487 --> 00:43:37,114
I'll remove my hand now.

608
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:39,450
Don't scream.

609
00:43:39,533 --> 00:43:40,993
Don't follow me.

610
00:43:42,036 --> 00:43:42,953
Got it?

611
00:44:02,514 --> 00:44:03,515
I'm going.

612
00:44:05,142 --> 00:44:06,310
Hurry, this way.

613
00:44:36,507 --> 00:44:37,883
Hurry up.

614
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:42,680
Why is no one here?

615
00:44:43,430 --> 00:44:46,100
I'll go check the rehearsal.
The waiting room is that way.

616
00:44:52,815 --> 00:44:55,734
How is he the one late
to his own solo concert?

617
00:44:56,568 --> 00:45:00,322
-He has no manners at all.
-He's been busy lately.

618
00:45:00,406 --> 00:45:02,950
Solo promotions, variety shows, and radio…

619
00:45:04,493 --> 00:45:05,661
I feel bad for him.

620
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:09,540
It seems like he's always carrying
everything by himself.

621
00:45:09,623 --> 00:45:10,624
Young-bin,

622
00:45:10,707 --> 00:45:13,168
you don't know
what that psycho's been doing, do you?

623
00:45:13,252 --> 00:45:14,545
What have I been doing?

624
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:17,131
You're here?

625
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:19,466
What's that psycho supposedly doing?

626
00:45:20,092 --> 00:45:21,635
Dating? Gambling?

627
00:45:21,718 --> 00:45:23,720
Drugs? What?

628
00:45:23,804 --> 00:45:25,472
Why are you so late?

629
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:27,057
Can the main character be this late?

630
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:30,936
-Jae-hee!
-He showed up late and didn't say sorry.

631
00:45:32,312 --> 00:45:34,356
I'm sorry, happy now?

632
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,108
You should say thanks too.

633
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:40,070
You dragged us here
since you had no guests.

634
00:45:40,154 --> 00:45:41,530
Hey, come on.

635
00:45:41,613 --> 00:45:42,823
Seriously!

636
00:45:44,783 --> 00:45:46,201
It's true, right?

637
00:45:46,743 --> 00:45:49,621
You're using us because you can't handle
filling two hours by yourself.

638
00:45:51,373 --> 00:45:52,332
Aren't you?

639
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:53,292
WAITING ROOM / GOLD BOYS  (KANG WOO-SEONG,
CHOI JAE-HEE, LEE YOUNG-BIN)

640
00:45:53,959 --> 00:45:55,252
You're right.

641
00:45:55,335 --> 00:45:56,670
I'm using you.

642
00:45:57,254 --> 00:45:58,714
But you're no different, are you?

643
00:45:58,797 --> 00:46:01,383
Your contract's expiring,
you're getting zero offers,

644
00:46:02,217 --> 00:46:03,927
and the only way to survive is to renew.

645
00:46:04,011 --> 00:46:06,513
So you've been doing
whatever the company says

646
00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:08,265
and came all the way here.

647
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:10,559
Trying to cling to me
for a few more years.

648
00:46:10,642 --> 00:46:12,561
What? What did you just say?

649
00:46:13,687 --> 00:46:14,855
Kang Woo-seong, see?

650
00:46:14,938 --> 00:46:16,356
This is why I said no.

651
00:46:18,150 --> 00:46:21,320
All right, I'm done.

652
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:27,242
-I'm done being this lunatic's lackey.
-Hey, Jae-hee.

653
00:46:27,326 --> 00:46:28,744
-Hey!
-Yes, go!

654
00:46:29,620 --> 00:46:32,122
I'm glad I won't have to see
you ruin my stage.

655
00:46:33,332 --> 00:46:34,791
You are the one, screw it.

656
00:46:35,792 --> 00:46:37,878
You think you got a solo
because of your skill?

657
00:46:37,961 --> 00:46:41,089
No, but do you know why?

658
00:46:41,173 --> 00:46:43,509
It's all thanks to that cheap sob story
you keep selling.

659
00:46:43,592 --> 00:46:46,553
What's so great about suffering
under a mom who worked at a bar?

660
00:46:46,637 --> 00:46:48,639
Hey, Choi Jae-hee!

661
00:46:48,722 --> 00:46:52,059
-Hey, say it again.
-I'm telling the truth.

662
00:46:52,142 --> 00:46:54,811
You sell your sad past for pity points!

663
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:57,189
-Say it again!
-Hold on.

664
00:46:57,981 --> 00:47:00,484
People don't love you.

665
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:02,361
They just pity you.

666
00:47:02,903 --> 00:47:04,488
-What a bastard!
-Ra-ik!

667
00:47:04,571 --> 00:47:06,406
Stop!

668
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:07,533
Wait a sec…

669
00:47:09,243 --> 00:47:11,912
-Come here!
-Choi Jae-hee!

670
00:47:13,539 --> 00:47:14,915
Calm down, Ra-ik.

671
00:47:14,998 --> 00:47:16,083
Move!

672
00:47:18,252 --> 00:47:19,836
Move out!

673
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:23,465
-Please, stop!
-Move out!

674
00:47:24,091 --> 00:47:26,510
-Young-bin!
-Please stop fighting!

675
00:47:30,472 --> 00:47:31,598
Are you okay?

676
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:48,031
Get inside, the concert starts soon.

677
00:47:48,824 --> 00:47:50,200
Take care of Ra-ik.

678
00:47:50,784 --> 00:47:51,660
Ra-ik, come on.

679
00:48:04,256 --> 00:48:06,341
SUCCESSFUL CONCERT
RECORD-BREAKING AUDIENCE

680
00:49:03,315 --> 00:49:05,192
Why weren't the other members
there yesterday?

681
00:49:05,275 --> 00:49:06,610
I was expecting a guest.

682
00:49:06,693 --> 00:49:09,363
They were supposed to come out,
but they fought and got hurt.

683
00:49:09,446 --> 00:49:12,658
I was working yesterday
and saw Ra-ik and Jae-hee fighting.

684
00:49:12,741 --> 00:49:15,577
They came to help his solo concert
and he behaves like that?

685
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:16,495
His attitude hit rock bottom.

686
00:49:17,162 --> 00:49:18,455
What are they talking about?

687
00:49:20,332 --> 00:49:22,668
False rumor dissemination fine--

688
00:49:22,751 --> 00:49:23,669
MESSAGE

689
00:49:26,338 --> 00:49:27,422
LIKE

690
00:49:28,131 --> 00:49:29,466
Did you see the comments?

691
00:49:31,093 --> 00:49:32,469
Yeah.

692
00:49:32,552 --> 00:49:36,264
What is this Gold Boys discord rumor?
Is the Ra-ik personality controversy real?

693
00:49:36,348 --> 00:49:38,850
What? LIKE.

694
00:49:39,935 --> 00:49:41,019
How can even you…

695
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:47,359
Discord rumors are nothing new.
Our boys really are close.

696
00:49:52,155 --> 00:49:53,490
It's all over communities.

697
00:49:54,783 --> 00:49:57,119
They say Ra-ik beat them,
so they ended up in the ER.

698
00:49:58,829 --> 00:50:00,288
That makes no sense.

699
00:50:01,206 --> 00:50:06,670
GOLD BOYS RUMORS OF DISCORD
DO RA-IK CONTROVERSY COMPILATION

700
00:50:13,009 --> 00:50:14,594
DON'T STICK

701
00:50:14,678 --> 00:50:15,554
DON'T STICK TO ME

702
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:17,264
EMBARRASSED

703
00:50:18,140 --> 00:50:19,141
This is…

704
00:50:20,267 --> 00:50:21,101
ANNOYED

705
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:23,603
I want to defend him too, but…

706
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:25,313
My eyes aren't blurred anymore…

707
00:50:26,064 --> 00:50:29,526
I don't know if the Ra-ik I loved
is even the real him.

708
00:50:31,319 --> 00:50:33,822
Sellpish, do you trust him?

709
00:50:33,905 --> 00:50:34,781
DON'T ACT UP

710
00:50:34,865 --> 00:50:37,284
Do you trust him 100%?

711
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:57,596
I trust him.

712
00:50:59,848 --> 00:51:02,267
I trust our Ra-ik

713
00:51:08,231 --> 00:51:14,321
I'm still me, just as I've always been

714
00:51:14,404 --> 00:51:19,034
Not once have I ever been
Anyone but myself

715
00:51:19,117 --> 00:51:21,286
I'm still

716
00:51:21,369 --> 00:51:23,997
The same as you know me

717
00:51:24,080 --> 00:51:26,249
There is nothing less

718
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:29,294
There is nothing more

719
00:51:29,377 --> 00:51:30,670
Enough already.

720
00:51:30,754 --> 00:51:32,422
It's me

721
00:51:32,506 --> 00:51:34,090
The security office will call!

722
00:51:40,055 --> 00:51:42,265
Woo-seong's here.

723
00:51:52,108 --> 00:51:54,110
Come in.

724
00:51:54,194 --> 00:51:55,987
What's all this alcohol?

725
00:51:56,071 --> 00:51:57,781
It's been a while for us guys.

726
00:52:00,033 --> 00:52:02,285
Hold on, then I'll bring out some snacks.

727
00:52:02,369 --> 00:52:04,246
It's fine, it's already past eight.

728
00:52:04,329 --> 00:52:06,081
It'll be quick.

729
00:52:06,164 --> 00:52:08,542
-Go before it gets later.
-All right.

730
00:52:08,625 --> 00:52:10,085
Stop chugging alcohol.

731
00:52:10,168 --> 00:52:13,296
If you whine tomorrow about heartburn,
I will throw bread chunks at you.

732
00:52:13,380 --> 00:52:14,965
All right.

733
00:52:15,674 --> 00:52:16,633
-Go.
-Yeah.

734
00:52:22,264 --> 00:52:23,974
He looks completely deflated.

735
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:29,145
I'll cook hangover soup tomorrow,
so sleep over.

736
00:52:29,229 --> 00:52:30,605
-Be safe.
-Okay.

737
00:52:35,610 --> 00:52:38,822
Why are you here? What about the boys?
What about Jae-hee?

738
00:52:39,656 --> 00:52:41,533
So you do worry, huh?

739
00:52:43,201 --> 00:52:46,663
I worry he might still be alive
when I should have finished him.

740
00:52:46,746 --> 00:52:49,749
You came to the hospital.
I know everything.

741
00:53:00,385 --> 00:53:02,971
You rushed over after the concert
because you were worried.

742
00:53:03,054 --> 00:53:04,472
You didn't even go to the after party.

743
00:53:04,556 --> 00:53:07,350
You could've at least said hello
since you came, seriously.

744
00:53:07,976 --> 00:53:11,354
You were all talking behind my back
so how could I show up there?

745
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:13,315
Luckily, he was not badly hurt.

746
00:53:13,398 --> 00:53:15,191
Just a cast, he will be discharged soon.

747
00:53:21,656 --> 00:53:23,700
Jae-hee really feels sorry.

748
00:53:24,534 --> 00:53:27,245
He knows he should never have said--

749
00:53:30,498 --> 00:53:32,375
This is expensive, chew it and swallow.

750
00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:57,776
Hey, this tastes just like that, right?

751
00:53:59,277 --> 00:54:01,905
When we lived in the semi-basement room…

752
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:05,033
the one with a month past its expiration.

753
00:54:05,617 --> 00:54:07,661
Yeah, that chunky milk.

754
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:09,996
-It tastes exactly the same.
-Right.

755
00:54:10,538 --> 00:54:12,916
You drank it
because you didn't want to waste it,

756
00:54:12,999 --> 00:54:14,709
and then right before the stage…

757
00:54:22,467 --> 00:54:25,053
Back then, we were passionate.

758
00:54:27,263 --> 00:54:28,598
No matter how sick we were,

759
00:54:28,682 --> 00:54:33,311
all we wanted was to be on the stage.

760
00:54:42,821 --> 00:54:46,241
Ra-ik, if it's too hard for you…

761
00:54:46,324 --> 00:54:47,617
If it's too hard, then what?

762
00:54:49,494 --> 00:54:52,247
You know about my mom.

763
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:57,877
Hey, we really need to work hard.

764
00:54:57,961 --> 00:55:02,424
Kids these days think
Gold Boys is the name of an animation.

765
00:55:06,970 --> 00:55:08,179
So,

766
00:55:09,764 --> 00:55:13,143
you are thinking
of continuing Gold Boys then?

767
00:55:14,936 --> 00:55:15,979
Didn't you see

768
00:55:17,230 --> 00:55:18,356
my album performance?

769
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:21,735
Jae-hee was right.

770
00:55:22,694 --> 00:55:25,196
I cannot do it alone.

771
00:55:27,115 --> 00:55:28,616
People love

772
00:55:29,325 --> 00:55:30,994
Ra-ik of Gold Boys,

773
00:55:31,578 --> 00:55:34,622
not just Do Ra-ik.

774
00:55:36,207 --> 00:55:39,711
So I have to remain Gold Boys to the end.

775
00:55:42,505 --> 00:55:45,633
Stop the depressing talk, let's drink.

776
00:56:34,974 --> 00:56:36,101
Woo-seong.

777
00:57:25,650 --> 00:57:27,694
Woo-seong

778
00:57:28,236 --> 00:57:32,782
Woo-seong!

779
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:34,951
Woo-seong!

780
00:57:38,037 --> 00:57:40,081
Open your eyes!

781
00:57:40,707 --> 00:57:41,833
What happened to you?

782
00:57:43,084 --> 00:57:44,335
Woo-seong.

783
00:57:45,545 --> 00:57:46,838
What am I supposed to do?

784
00:57:47,505 --> 00:57:49,382
Woo-seong!

785
00:58:18,828 --> 00:58:19,954
There are days like that.

786
00:58:20,788 --> 00:58:23,625
Days when I dreamed about you…

787
00:58:27,128 --> 00:58:28,379
and on those days,

788
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:32,050
I can't help falling
into foolish little fantasies.

789
00:58:36,596 --> 00:58:41,768
Like accidentally sharing a table
with you at a random restaurant,

790
00:58:47,232 --> 00:58:51,152
or bumping into you
alone in an empty, late-night theater.

791
00:58:53,738 --> 00:58:56,658
Just imagining it makes me happy.

792
00:58:58,910 --> 00:59:01,496
FRESH MILK

793
00:59:07,293 --> 00:59:09,379
Ra-ik is at Gangseo Police Station
right now.

794
00:59:17,554 --> 00:59:19,847
RA-IK MURDERED WOO-SEONG?

795
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:30,858
Shock spreads as Gold Boys member

796
00:59:30,942 --> 00:59:33,987
Kang Woo-seong was found dead.

797
00:59:34,070 --> 00:59:37,657
The core of the incident
is that his body was found

798
00:59:37,740 --> 00:59:42,370
at fellow member Ra-ik's residence
in Gangseong, Seoul.

799
00:59:42,453 --> 00:59:43,830
Police confirmed

800
00:59:43,913 --> 00:59:46,499
that the two were together
on the day of the incident,

801
00:59:46,583 --> 00:59:49,877
and have identified him
as the primary suspect.

802
00:59:49,961 --> 00:59:52,463
He was arrested on site

803
00:59:52,547 --> 00:59:54,674
and is currently
at the Gangseo Police Station.

804
00:59:54,757 --> 00:59:56,426
And I imagine,

805
00:59:57,552 --> 01:00:00,805
just once, a miracle like that

806
01:00:01,681 --> 01:00:04,434
could happen to me too.

807
01:00:05,852 --> 01:00:07,228
POLICE STATION

808
01:00:07,312 --> 01:00:08,563
LAWYER'S ID

809
01:00:15,445 --> 01:00:18,114
LAWYER'S RECEPTION ROOM

810
01:00:35,882 --> 01:00:36,924
But…

811
01:00:38,593 --> 01:00:40,345
even if I imagined it

812
01:00:41,471 --> 01:00:43,681
a hundred times, a thousand times,

813
01:00:45,099 --> 01:00:46,100
I never imagined

814
01:00:53,691 --> 01:00:55,943
that we would meet…

815
01:00:58,613 --> 01:01:00,865
as a lawyer and a murder suspect.

816
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:54,877
You tell me, who is Do Ra-ik?

817
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:57,839
Why are you so obsessed with this case?

818
01:01:57,922 --> 01:01:59,632
There are many contradictions in the case.

819
01:02:00,174 --> 01:02:01,551
There's definitely something there.

820
01:02:02,176 --> 01:02:04,554
Criminal Division 3, Seoul Central
District Prosecutors' Office

821
01:02:04,637 --> 01:02:05,722
Kwak Byung-gyun.

822
01:02:05,805 --> 01:02:08,558
Guys like Kang Woo-seong
are always unlucky jerks.

823
01:02:08,641 --> 01:02:10,977
What do you mean you dropped Ra-ik's case?

824
01:02:11,060 --> 01:02:12,395
He's going to trial without a lawyer.

825
01:02:12,478 --> 01:02:13,646
Do you realize?

826
01:02:13,730 --> 01:02:14,939
But what if it really was me?

827
01:02:15,481 --> 01:02:17,567
No matter how hard I try,
I can't remember.

828
01:02:17,650 --> 01:02:22,655
